y%209%2C%202024.%3Cp%3ESelcuk%20Acar%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b0057c45-2254-4899-9298-6768f7817a02%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EImmigrants%20boost%20home%20values%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20politicians%20with%20anti-immigrant%20views%20and%20others%20have%20long%20sought%20to%20stoke%20xenophobia%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fshow%2Ftrump-under-fire-again-for-violent-language-and-dehumanizing-anti-immigrant-rhetoric%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemonizing%20immigrants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20immigrant-heavy%20neighborhoods%20across%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newamericaneconomy.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2013%2F09%2Frevival-of-american-cities.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20thrived%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForeign-born%20residents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F00111287211007736%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20neighborhoods%20safer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FABC_Univision%2FPolitics%2Freport-immigrants-revitalize-neighborhoods-homeowners-investing-trillions%2Fstory%3Fid%3D19445130%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewealthier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20part%20by%20boosting%20home%20values.%20Immigrants%20have%20long%20helped%20keep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.census.gov%2Fprod2%2F3%2F98pubs%2Fcenbr974.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20US%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20strong%20and%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20stabilizing%20it%20following%20the%20Great%20Recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20do%20newly%20immigrant-heavy%20neighborhoods%20tend%20to%20see%20their%20home%20prices%20and%20rents%20increase%2C%20but%20surrounding%20areas%20see%20their%20housing%20costs%20and%20values%20rise%20even%20more%2C%20Susan%20Pozo%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20Western%20Michigan%20University%2C%20and%20her%20colleagues%20found%20in%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1051137717300025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20reason%20behind%20this%20uptick%20is%20likely%20that%20many%20native-born%20residents%20leave%20for%20surrounding%20areas%2C%20pushing%20up%20demand%20there%2C%20Pozo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20immigration%20might%20have%20a%20disinflationary%20impact%20on%20the%20housing%20market%20because%20new%20arrivals%20disproportionately%20work%20in%20the%20construction%20industry%2C%20helping%20solve%20the%20housing%20shortage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BImmigration%20tends%20to%20raise%20local%20rents%20but%20slow%20inflation%20modestly%20in%20other%20core%20categories%2C%20resulting%20in%20little%20net%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20researchers%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20wrote%20in%20a%20research%20note%20published%20on%20May%205.%20%26quot%3BSince%20housing%20construction%20has%20been%20constrained%20for%20the%20last%20decade%20by%20labor%20shortages%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20new%20immigrants%20will%20eventually%20do%20more%20to%20boost%20housing%20supply%20than%20housing%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22acfd17e8-a3d1-4a6c-a716-8af016283bfc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPushing%20migrants%20out%20of%20shelters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City%20has%20managed%20to%20absorb%20much%20larger%20influxes%20of%20immigrants%20in%20the%20past.%20In%201907%2C%203%2C400%20people%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fideas%2Farchive%2F2024%2F02%2Fasylum-seekers-migrant-crisis%2F677464%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprocessed%20at%20Ellis%20Island%20every%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20average.%20Right%20now%2C%20an%20average%20of%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Foffice-of-the-mayor%2Fnews%2F780-23%2Fas-number-asylum-seekers-city-s-care-tops-64-100-city-additional-policies-for%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E600%20migrants%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20arriving%20in%20the%20city%20each%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20last%20month%2C%20the%20city%20government%20amended%20its%20right-to-shelter%20law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F15%2Fnyregion%2Fnyc-right-to-shelter-homeless-migrants.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannouncing%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20will%20begin%20forcing%20single%20adult%20migrants%20out%20of%20shelters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecity.nyc%2F2024%2F04%2F26%2Fmigrants-shelter-extension-exception%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eafter%2030%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20some%20families%20with%20children%20will%20be%20limited%20to%2060%20days%20in%20a%20shelter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20City%20comptroller's%20office%20says%20the%20Adams%20administration%20is%20intentionally%20making%20life%20more%20difficult%20for%20asylum-seekers%20as%20a%20way%20to%20force%20them%20out%20of%20the%20city.%20Without%20legal%20documents%2C%20migrants%20aren't%20eligible%20for%20other%20government%20housing%20assistance%2C%20like%20vouchers%20or%20public%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20policies%20are%20intentionally%20designed%20basically%20to%20just%20make%20it%20frustrating%20for%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Celeste%20Hornbach%2C%20director%20of%20housing%20policy%20in%20the%20New%20York%20City%20comptroller's%20office.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20just%20a%20system%20that%20is%20meant%20to%20really%20discourage%20people%20from%20getting%20help%20from%20the%20city%20and%20from%20exercising%20their%20rights%20that%20they%20have%20as%20residents%20of%20New%20York%20City.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20has%20also%20failed%20to%20provide%20proper%20case%20management%20for%20thousands%20of%20migrants%2C%20and%20rarely%20follows%20up%20with%20families%20and%20individuals%20after%20they've%20left%20the%20shelter%20system%2C%20experts%20in%20the%20comptroller's%20office%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20case%20management%20the%20city%20has%20stood%20up%20is%20more%20focused%20on%20just%20getting%20people%20out%20of%20the%20shelter%2C%20rather%20than%20stabilizing%20them%20and%20helping%20them%20succeed%20once%20they're%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sam%20Stanton%2C%20a%20senior%20policy%20researcher%20in%20the%20comptroller's%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20where%20many%20go%20once%20they%20leave%20the%20shelters%2C%20Hornbach%20said%2C%20but%20some%20likely%20end%20up%20in%20substandard%20%26quot%3Bgray%20market%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20in%20basements%20or%20other%20potentially%20unsafe%2C%20overcrowded%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20local%2C%20state%2C%20and%20federal%20efforts%20to%20build%20more%20housing%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20affordable%20homes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0communities%20across%20the%20country%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20sustain%20dynamic%20economies%20and%20vibrant%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigrants-boost-us-economy-housing-shortage-hurts-growth-nyc-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715162581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662ff0ca0dfb1341e90078bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigrants-boost-us-economy-housing-shortage-hurts-growth-nyc-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20US%20handles%20an%20uptick%20in%20asylum-seekers%2C%20pressure%20is%20mounting%20to%20solve%20the%20housing%20crisis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigrants-boost-us-economy-housing-shortage-hurts-growth-nyc-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Isabelle%20Huppert%20to%20Head%20Venice%20Film%20Festival%20Jury%2