ico-from-us-merida-safety-cost-healthcare-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMexico%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20visits%20to%20the%20US%20just%20prior%20to%20moving%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20knew%20they%20wanted%20to%20go%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bwild%20adventure%26quot%3B%20before%20they%20had%20kids%2C%20though%20they%20also%20wanted%20to%20work%20during%20their%20trip%20to%20supplement%20the%20costs.%20After%20some%20research%2C%20they%20determined%20they%20could%20live%20comfortably%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-work-culture-love-hate-relationship-tech-worker-relocation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20find%20employment%20despite%20the%20language%20barrier%2C%20as%20neither%20speaks%20fluent%20Mandarin%20or%20Cantonese.%20Despite%20some%20opposition%20from%20his%20family%20and%20friends%2C%20they%20predicted%20their%20experiences%20would%20be%20better%20than%20what%20many%20anticipated%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20wife%20got%20a%20job%20as%20a%20teacher%20at%20an%20international%20school%2C%20and%20the%20two%20moved%20to%20China%20on%20her%20visa.%20Although%20he%20had%20never%20taught%2C%20Vleeschouwer%20also%20secured%20a%20position%20at%20the%20school.%20They%20moved%20eight%20months%20ago%20to%20Dapeng%2C%20a%20suburb%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-costco-location-shenzhen-hong-kong-shoppers-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShenzhen%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20beach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20allows%20both%20of%20them%20to%20take%20more%20time%20off%20than%20corporate%20positions%20due%20to%20various%20breaks%2C%20festivals%2C%20and%20holidays.%20They%20get%20two%20weeks%20off%20for%20spring%20break%20and%20Christmas%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20summer%20vacation%2C%20which%20has%20allowed%20them%20to%20visit%20Beijing%20and%20Shanghai.%20They%20have%20also%20traveled%20to%20India%2C%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-millennial-moved-america-philippines-slow-life-debt-free-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhilippines%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20booked%20trips%20to%20Indonesia%20and%20Kenya.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20access%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20places%20down%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%20that%20are%20pretty%20quick%2C%20short%2C%20affordable%20flights%2C%26quot%3B%20Vleeschouwer%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20realize%20that%20we%20would%20have%20this%20many%20cool%20places%20to%20travel%20to%20so%20close.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%20of%20living%20in%20China%20compared%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20wife's%20base%20salary%20in%20China%20is%20more%20than%20she%20made%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20the%20school%20pays%20for%20their%20healthcare%20and%20housing.%20Their%20flight%20to%20China%20was%20also%20paid%20for%2C%20and%20the%20school%20provided%20them%20with%20free%20lunches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20moving%20to%20China%2C%20the%20couple%20paid%20%241%2C900%20a%20month%20in%20rent%20in%20Arizona.%20They%20still%20own%20and%20maintain%20two%20rental%20homes%20in%20the%20US.%20He%20said%20their%20internet%20bill%20was%20%24130%20a%20month%2C%20their%20cellphone%20bill%20was%20%2470%2C%20and%20their%20electricity%20bill%20was%20%24100.%20He%20said%20they%20spend%20about%20%24500%20to%20%24600%20a%20month%20on%20groceries%2C%20and%20their%20car%20insurance%20costs%20%24100%20monthly%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20%24130%20a%20month%20in%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20China%2C%20bicycles%20and%20e-scooters%20are%20the%20most%20common%20form%20of%20transportation%2C%20which%20saves%20them%20over%20%241%2C000%20a%20year.%20They%20estimate%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20decent%20e-scooter%20to%20be%20%24300.%20They%20occasionally%20take%20DiDi%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Chinese%20equivalent%20of%20Uber%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20only%20%241%20to%20%242%20to%20their%20workplace%20or%20%2430%20round-trip%20to%20the%20city's%20downtown%2C%20about%20an%20hour%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20paid%20rent%20on%20their%20three-bedroom%20apartment%2C%20it%20would%20amount%20to%20about%20%24800%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20phone%20bill%20is%20%2427%20monthly%20for%20three%20lines%20and%2045%20gigabytes%20of%20data.%20Their%20three-month%20water%20bill%20was%20just%20%249.%20They%20spend%20about%20%2430%20a%20week%20on%20groceries%2C%20frequently%20purchasing%20fresh%20fruit%2C%20fish%2C%20and%20rice.%20He%20said%20they%20shop%20at%20an%20expat%20grocery%20store%20that's%20fairly%20Westernized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdjusting%20to%20cultural%20differences%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVleeschouwer%20said%20it's%20taken%20him%20some%20time%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcultural-differences-us-china-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadjust%20to%20cultural%20norms%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20he%20tries%20to%20improve%20his%20language%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he's%20trying%20to%20pick%20up%20on%20phrases%20and%20expressions%20to%20get%20around%20easily%2C%20he%20often%20relies%20on%20technology%20that%20automatically%20translates%20signs%20and%20labels.%20He%20also%20uses%20translation%20apps%20for%20communicating%20with%20people%20who%20don't%20speak%20English%2C%20which%20is%20very%20common%20in%20his%20more%20rural%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20languages%20are%20very%20difficult%20to%20learn%20as%20an%20outsider%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20teach%20yourself%20a%20word%2C%20and%20you%20say%20it%20again%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20understand%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20able%20to%20access%20many%20apps%20on%20his%20VPN%20that%20are%20otherwise%20blocked%20by%20the%20government%2C%20which%20has%20allowed%20him%20to%20stay%20in%20better%20contact%20with%20friends%20and%20family%20in%20the%20US.%20Still%2C%20he%20misses%20having%20full%20access%20to%20the%20internet%20that%20he%20had%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20slowly%20adjusted%20to%20restaurants%20not%20offering%20cold%20water%20and%20dining%20being%20community-style.%20He%20doesn't%20drink%20tap%20water%2C%20as%20boiling%20it%20before%20drinking%20is%20recommended.%20He%20also%20knows%20to%20take%20off%20his%20shoes%20before%20entering%20someone%20else's%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20he%20can%20get%20most%20of%20what%20he%20needs%20in%20his%20area%2C%20he%20misses%20the%20brands%20he's%20come%20to%20love%20in%20the%20US.%20Getting%20products%20like%20medicine%20or%20vitamins%20or%20hair%20products%20takes%20some%20time%20to%20select%20due%20to%20the%20language%20barrier%2C%20as%20most%20brands%20are%20China-specific.%20He%20said%20in%20Shenzhen%20proper%2C%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20more%20Western%20stores%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20larger%20expat%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20felt%20very%20welcomed%20by%20those%20at%20his%20school%20and%20many%20in%20his%20community%2C%20though%20he%20said%20locals%20are%20sometimes%20confused%20about%20why%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20live%20so%20far%20outside%20of%20the%20city.%20They've%20made%20some%20good%20friends%20in%20China%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20from%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20stick%20out%20like%20a%20sore%20thumb%2C%20and%20everyone%20stares%20at%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Vleeschouwer%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20literally%20eat%20dinner%20and%20kids%20will%20come%20up%20and%20put%20chairs%20next%20to%20us%20and%20just%20watch%20us%20eat%20dinner.%20We%20held%20someone's%20baby%20once%3B%20they%20just%20handed%20us%20their%20baby%20because%20they%20wanted%20a%20picture%20of%20their%20baby%20with%20a%20white%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20he%20enjoys%20doing%20the%20more%20touristy%20things%20like%20hiking%20the%20Great%20Wall%20of%20China%20or%20visiting%20Shanghai%2C%20parts%20of%20which%20reminded%20him%20of%20the%20US.%20He%20said%20the%20scale%20of%20cities%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bunfathomable%20high%20rises%26quot%3B%20in%20China%20also%20shocked%20him.%20Not%20having%20easy%20access%20to%20a%20car%2C%20though%2C%20is%20sometimes%20tough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20are%20kind%20of%20locked%20where%20we%20are%20compared%20to%20what%20we're%20used%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Vleeschouwer%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20like%20city%20life%2C%20except%20we%20just%20can't%20go%20anywhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20plan%20to%20stay%20in%20China%20for%20two%20years%20per%20his%20wife's%20contract%2C%20then%20they're%20not%20sure%20where%20to%20go%20next.%20They%20may%20stay%20in%20China%2C%20which%20he%20said%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Breally%20good%20place%20to%20have%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20given%20six%20months%20of%20paid%20maternity%20leave%20in%20his%20city.%20Still%2C%20they've%20considered%20going%20back%20to%20living%20on%20a%20sailboat%20in%20Mexico%20or%20building%20a%20homestead%20in%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20recently%20moved%20to%20a%20new%20country%20or%20state%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-china-leaving-arizona-shenzhen-phoenix-cost-of-living-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715162042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6633f1ed10dfcda40966360f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-china-leaving-arizona-shenzhen-phoenix-cost-of-living-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scott%20and%20Marissa%20Vleeschouwer%20relocated%20from%20Arizona%20to%20China%20to%20work%20at%20an%20international%20school%2C%20and%20they%20enjoy%20the%20lower%20cost%20of%20living.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-china-leaving-arizona-shenzhen-phoenix-cost-of-living-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20son%20died%2015%20years%20ago%20while%20playing%20in%20a%20pool.%20It%20changed%20me.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20by%20a%20pool%20talking%20to%20kids%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a552cec0c69656901d276%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(right)%20started%20a%20foundation%20after%20her%20son%20drowned%20in%20a%20pool%20to%20help%20educate%20other%20parents%20about%20water%20safety.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIn%202007%20my%20son%20Zachary%20drowned%20after%20his%20arm%20got%20stuck%20in%20the%20drain%20of%20the%20pool.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20had%20done%20everything%20I%20thought%20was%20needed%20for%20water%20safety%2C%20from%20swim%20lessons%20to%20having%20an%20adult%20nearby.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20started%20a%20foundation%20to%20help%20other%20parents%20learn%20about%20water%20safety.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2028%2C%202007%2C%20my%20family's%20life%20changed%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20scorching%20summer%20afternoon%20at%20our%20new%20home.%20We%20sat%20around%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbackyard-pool-bad-investment-best-purchase-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebackyard%20pool%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20closely%20watched%20as%20our%206-year-old%20son%2C%20Zachary%2C%20showed%20off%20his%20swimming%20skills%20while%20I%20rocked%20our%202-month-old%20daughter%2C%20Sydney%2C%20in%20my%20arms.%20There%20was%20no%20sign%20of%20the%20tragedy%20that%20was%20about%20to%20unfold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20peaceful%20afternoon%20was%20shattered%20by%20screams%20and%20chaos.%20Zachary's%20arm%20had%20become%20entrapped%20by%20the%20powerful%20suction%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fswimming-pool-loans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrain%20in%20the%20pool%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20I%20raced%20to%20shut%20the%20power%20off%2C%20my%20husband%2C%20Brian%2C%20dove%20in%20to%20rescue%20Zachary.%20Tragically%2C%20no%20one%20could%20override%20the%20several%20hundreds%20of%20pounds%20of%20suction%20from%20the%20drain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221154%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Little%20boy%20on%20a%20boat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a59dfb8f515beaf1257a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20son's%20arm%20got%20stuck%20in%20a%20pool%20drain.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20parents%2C%20we%20thought%20we%20did%20everything%20we%20could%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwater-swim-safety-tips-prevent-drowning-parents-kids-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotect%20our%20child%20from%20drowning%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20enrolled%20him%20in%20swimming%20classes%2C%20explained%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20pool%2C%20and%20ensured%20he%20was%20always%20supervised%20by%20an%20adult.%20Until%20then%2C%20we%20were%20unaware%20of%20the%20potential%20dangers%20below%20the%20surface.%20It%20was%20that%20summer%20that%20our%20family%20and%20neighbors%20learned%20of%20the%20dangers%20of%20%26quot%3Bdrain%20entrapment%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20term%20that%20will%20forever%20haunt%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c33faff4-bde6-457a-87c8-860a3cd06017%5C%22%3EWe%20started%20a%20foundation%20to%20help%20other%20parents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-support-grieving-parents-after-the-loss-of-child-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emidst%20of%20our%20grief%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20that%20we%20wanted%20to%20spare%20other%20families%20from%20the%20pain%20and%20loss%20we%20experienced%20on%20that%20day%20and%20every%20day%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20promise%20led%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthezacfoundation.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZAC%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202008%20with%20a%20vision%20for%20generational%20change%20in%20how%20water%20safety%20is%20viewed%20by%20parents%20and%20their%20children.%20The%20ZAC%20Foundation%20believes%20addressing%20the%20nation's%20drowning%20crisis%20requires%20a%20whole%20community%20approach%20informed%20by%2C%20and%20reflective%20of%2C%20the%20realities%20specific%20to%20individual%20communities%2C%20including%20the%20makeup%20of%20the%20local%20population%20and%20cultural%20attitudes%20toward%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-signs-of-unsafe-swimming-water-toxic-algae-stomach-viruses-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewater%20safety%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Foundation%20has%20provided%20water%20safety%20programming%20through%20its%20award-winning%20ZAC%20Camps%20to%20more%20than%2020%2C000%20children%20ages%205%20to%209%20in%20at-risk%20communities%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%2015%20years%20have%20been%20an%20education%20in%20the%20pervasive%20nature%20of%20water%20threats.%20We%20are%20reminded%20daily%20that%20parents'%20best%20intentions%20are%20no%20match%20for%20unmitigated%20danger%20and%20lack%20of%20preparedness.%20It%20is%20not%20just%20a%20summertime%20issue%3B%20water%20safety%20is%20essential%20365%20days%20a%20year.%20According%20to%20the%20CDC%2C%20fatal%20drowning%20is%20so%20commonplace%20that%20it%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fdrowning%2Ffacts%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleading%20cause%20of%20death%20for%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20ages%201%20to%204%20and%20the%20second%20leading%20cause%20of%20unintentional%20injury%20death%20for%20children%205%20to%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChildren%20are%20quick%20and%20curious%2C%20and%20most%20drownings%20occur%20when%20a%20parent%20is%20not%20present.%20This%20includes%20children%20accessing%20backyard%20pools%20that%20aren't%20properly%20secured%2C%20unattended%20hot%20tubs%2C%20ponds%2C%20and%20even%20pet%20bowls%20of%20water.%20Babies%20can%20drown%20in%20as%20little%20as%20one%20inch%20of%20water%2C%20making%20it%20important%20to%20install%20barriers%20to%20bodies%20of%20water%20near%20the%20home%2C%20empty%20buckets%20of%20water%20when%20not%20in%20use%2C%20and%20lock%20the%20bathroom%20door%20to%20avoid%20access%20to%20the%20toilet%20and%20bathtub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22526caa65-4dd0-4ca4-8ae2-068e876092dc%5C%22%3EThere%20is%20no%20'off'%20season%20for%20water%20safety%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20write%20this%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20perceived%20%26quot%3Boffseason%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20urge%20readers%20to%20ensure%20homes%20are%20secured%20year-round%2C%20not%20just%20in%20the%20heat%20of%20summer.%20A%20checklist%20of%20water%20safety%20tips%20helps%20prevent%20tragedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20pool%20drains%20should%20comply%20with%20drain%20safety%20laws%2C%20which%20we%20helped%20enact%20after%20Zachary's%20death.%20An%20unsafe%20drain%20comes%20in%20many%20forms%2C%20including%20an%20extremely%20dangerous%20one%20that's%20missing%20a%20cover%20or%20one%20with%20a%20non-compliant%20cover.%20A%20safe%20drain%20has%20a%20raised%2C%20often%20dome-shaped%20cover%20with%20small%20openings%20that%20make%20it%20hard%20for%20hair%2C%20jewelry%2C%20and%20other%20loose%20items%20to%20get%20caught.%20When%20installed%20properly%2C%20compliant%20drain%20covers%20are%20the%20most%20effective%20way%20to%20protect%20children%20from%20entrapment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20barriers%20to%20the%20pool%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20four-sided%20fence%20with%20a%20locking%20gate%20%E2%80%94%20should%20effectively%20restrict%20children's%20access.%20Alarms%20on%20gates%20and%20doors%20leading%20to%20the%20pool%20area%20give%20an%20extra%20layer%20of%20protection%20as%20they%20provide%20an%20audible%20alert%20in%20addition%20to%20visuals.%20Finally%2C%20a%20secured%20pool%20cover%20that%20can%20withstand%20the%20weight%20of%20a%20child%20is%20another%20safety%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20physical%20barriers%20around%20pools%2C%20it's%20vital%20to%20equip%20families%20with%20the%20skills%20necessary%20for%20a%20lifetime%20of%20water%20safety.%20Enrolling%20children%20in%20swim%20lessons%20helps%20instill%20confidence%20and%20teaches%20lifesaving%20skills.%20Life%20jackets%20and%20personal%20flotation%20devices%20in%20water%20sports%20such%20as%20rafting%2C%20boating%2C%20and%20fishing%20are%20essential%20for%20everyone%2C%20even%20for%20sound%20swimmers%2C%20who%20can%20lose%20consciousness%20in%20an%20accident.%20And%20finally%2C%20CPR%20lessons%20for%20the%20entire%20family%20have%20a%20remarkable%20payoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20can%20save%20even%20one%20family%20from%20heartbreak%2C%20we%20will%20have%20honored%20Zachary's%20life%20and%20the%20window%20of%20joy%20he%20brought%20to%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchild-drowned-mom-started-foundation-teach-water-safety-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715161922000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a5536ec0c69656901d289%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchild-drowned-mom-started-foundation-teach-water-safety-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20son%20died%20after%20his%20arm%20got%20stuck