%20Ovide's%20(excellent)%20piece%20about%20the%20iPad%20revolution%20that%20never%20was%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20figured%20it%20was%20time%20to%20pony%20up%20again.%20I%20clicked%20on%20the%20polite%20message%20on%20the%20Post's%20site%20asking%20for%20new%20credit%20card%20info%20and%20prepared%20to%20give%20them%20%2412%20every%204%20weeks.%20Just%20like%20I%20had%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcept%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20only%20had%20to%20give%20them%20%242%20every%204%20weeks%2C%20for%20the%20next%20year.%20The%20Post%2C%20unprompted%2C%20said%20it%20was%20offering%20the%20discount%20because%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20inconvenience%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20again%2C%20was%20completely%20my%20own%20fault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221895%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20screenshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663aa0889686a6f37bfd0ec1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22520%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EWashington%20Post%2Fscreenshot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20well%20aware%20that%20anyone%20who%20runs%20a%20consumer%20subscription%20service%20spends%20a%20bunch%20of%20time%20on%20retention%20%E2%80%94%20trying%20to%20keep%20existing%20subscribers%20from%20churning%20out.%20(It's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-wins-streaming-wars-this-chart-shows-why-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparticularly%20acute%20issue%20for%20streamers%20right%20now%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20And%20that%20offering%20a%20discounted%20rate%20is%20one%20way%20those%20services%20try%20to%20keep%20a%20subscriber%20who%20tries%20to%20cancel%2C%20or%20to%20bring%20back%20one%20that's%20stopped%20paying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcept%3A%201)%20I%20didn't%20ask%20the%20Post%20for%20a%20discount%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20getting%20ready%20to%20pay%20full%20freight%20and%202)%20That%20is%20some%20discount%3A%2083%25%20of%20my%20old%20rate%2C%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20people%20who%20specialize%20in%20subscriber%20retention%20at%20places%20like%20the%20Post%2C%20so%20I'm%20sure%20they%20have%20thought%20this%20through.%20The%20most%20obvious%20answer%20is%20that%20it's%20a%20long-term%20bet%3A%20They%20think%20I'm%20one%20of%20those%20people%20who%20doesn't%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20looking%20at%20my%20credit%20card%20statements%2C%20and%20that%20in%20a%20year%2C%20when%20the%20Post%20starts%20charging%20me%20%2412%20again%2C%20I%20won't%20blink%20an%20eye.%20Ditto%20when%20they%20eventually%20raise%20prices.%20And%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20I've%20been%20a%20Post%20subscriber%20for%20several%20years%20indicates%20I'm%20likely%20to%20stick%20around%20for%20some%20time.%20(They%20would%20be%20correct%20in%20all%20of%20these%20assumptions.)%20There%20may%20also%20be%20people%20on%20their%20advertising%20side%20pushing%20them%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20subscribe%20because%20they%20think%20I'll%20be%20a%20more%20valuable%20advertising%20consumer%20than%20someone%20who's%20reading%20the%20Post%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I'm%20still%20surprised%20that%20the%20Post%2C%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F08%2F30%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fwashington-post-jeff-bezos-revenue.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewell-documented%20business%20struggles%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2023%2F12%2F19%2Fwashington-post-cut-jobs-voluntary-buyouts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpr%2F2023%2F11%2F04%2Fwashington-post-announces-william-lewis-publisher-ceo%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20willing%20to%20work%20so%20hard%20to%20keep%20me.%20It's%20a%20reminder%20of%20what%20a%20hard%20slog%20the%20subscription%20business%20is.%20Even%20if%20your%20owner%20is%20worth%20%24200%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdi