%20deaths.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmother-of-australian-brothers-killed-on-mexico-surfing-trip-says-world-a-darker-place-13131491%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmother-of-australian-brothers-killed-on-mexico-surfing-trip-says-world-a-darker-place-13131491%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmother-of-australian-brothers-killed-on-mexico-surfing-trip-says-world-a-darker-place-13131491%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22People%20Are%20Breathing%20In%20Cancer-Causing%20Chemicals%20In%20Their%20Cars%3A%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20breathing%20in%20cancer-causing%20chemicals%20when%20they're%20in%20their%20car%2C%20a%20new%20research%20has%20found.%20For%20the%20study%2C%20published%20in%20Environmental%20Science%20%26amp%3B%20Technology%2C%20researchers%20analysed%20the%20cabin%20air%20of%20101%20electric%2C%20gas%20and%20hybrid%20cars%20with%20a%20model%20year%20between%202015%20and%202022.%20They%20found%20that%2099%25%20of%20cars%20contained%20a%20flame%20retardant%20called%20TCIPP%2C%20which%20is%20under%20investigation%20by%20the%20US%20National%20Toxicology%20Program%20as%20a%20potential%20carcinogen.%20Most%20cars%20also%20had%20two%20more%20flame%20retardants%2C%20TDCIPP%20and%20TCEP%2C%20which%20are%20considered%20carcinogenic.%20These%20flame%20retardants%20are%20linked%20to%20neurological%20and%20reproductive%20harms%20as%20well%2C%20scientists%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsidering%20the%20average%20driver%20spends%20about%20an%20hour%20in%20the%20car%20every%20day%2C%20this%20is%20a%20significant%20public%20health%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rebecca%20Hoehn%2C%20lead%20researcher%20and%20toxicology%20scientist%20at%20Duke%20University%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeople.com%2Fdrivers-are-inhaling-cancer-causing-chemicals-in-their-cars-8644994%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPeople%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20particularly%20concerning%20for%20drivers%20with%20longer%20commutes%20as%20well%20as%20child%20passengers%2C%20who%20breathe%20more%20air%20pound%20for%20pound%20than%20adults%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.acs.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1021%2Facs.est.3c10440%5C%22%3Estudy%20%3C%2Fa%3Efound%20that%20the%20levels%20of%20toxic%20flame%20retardants%20were%20highest%20in%20the%20summer%20as%20heat%20increases%20the%20release%20of%20chemicals%20from%20the%20car%20materials.%20The%20researchers%20said%20that%20the%20source%20of%20the%20cancer-causing%20compounds%20in%20the%20cabin%20air%20is%20seat%20foam.%20Car%20manufacturers%20add%20the%20chemicals%20to%20seat%20foam%20and%20other%20materials%20to%20meet%20an%20%26quot%3Boutdated%26quot%3B%20flammability%20standard%20with%20no%20proven%20fire-safety%20benefit%2C%20they%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fcan-neckties-pose-health-hazard-heres-what-research-says-5608667%5C%22%3ECan%20Neckties%20Pose%20Health%20Hazard%3F%20Here's%20What%20Research%20Says%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Morrison%2C%20director%20of%20health%2C%20safety%20and%20medicine%20for%20the%20International%20Association%20of%20Fire%20Fighters%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BFirefighters%20are%20concerned%20that%20flame%20retardants%20contribute%20to%20their%20very%20high%20cancer%20rates.%20Filling%20products%20with%20these%20harmful%20chemicals%20does%20little%20to%20prevent%20fires%20for%20most%20uses%20and%20instead%20makes%20the%20blazes%20smokier%20and%20more%20toxic%20for%20victims%2C%20and%20especially%20for%20first%20responders%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20urge%20NHTSA%20(US%20National%20Highway%20Traffic%20Safety%2